Key Match Events: Netherlands beat Bangladesh by 87 runs in Kolkata
Scott Edwards scored 68 runs vs Bangladesh
Bangladesh knocked out of semi-finals race in CWC 2023
Wesley Barresi and Colin Akermann stitched an important 59-run stand
Bas de Leede and Edwards formed a 44-run partnership
Logan van Beek remained unbeaten on 23 runs off 16 balls
Shoriful Islam, Mahedi Hasan, Taskin and Mustafizur all picked two wickets each
Aryan Dutt got rid of Litton Das in the fifth over
Bangladesh lost six wickets with just 70 runs
Mahedi Hasan and Mahmudullah stitched a 38-run stand
Netherlands bundled Bangladesh over for 142 runs in 42.2 overs
Miscellaneous Highlights: Netherlands moved up to the eighth spot in the World Cup 2023 points table
Bangladesh slipped to ninth position in the points table
